    "question": "Vignette\n\nConsider the results of an analysis focusing on the market capitalizations of a sample of 100 firms:\n\nExhibit 1\nMarket Capitalization of a Sample of 100 Firms\nBin\tCumulative Percentage of Sample (%)\tMarket Capitalization (euro billions)\tNumber of Observations\nLower Bound\tUpper Bound\n1\t5\t0.28\t15.45\t5\n2\t10\t15.45\t21.22\t5\n3\t15\t21.22\t29.37\t5\n4\t20\t29.37\t32.57\t5\n5\t25\t32.57\t34.72\t5\n6\t30\t34.72\t37.58\t5\n7\t35\t37.58\t39.90\t5\n8\t40\t39.90\t41.57\t5\n9\t45\t41.57\t44.86\t5\n10\t50\t44.86\t46.88\t5\n11\t55\t46.88\t49.40\t5\n12\t60\t49.40\t51.27\t5\n13\t65\t51.27\t53.58\t5\n14\t70\t53.58\t56.66\t5\n15\t75\t56.66\t58.34\t5\n16\t80\t58.34\t63.10\t5\n17\t85\t63.10\t67.06\t5\n18\t90\t67.06\t73.00\t5\n19\t95\t73.00\t81.62\t5\n20\t100\t81.62\t96.85\t5\n\nThe tenth percentile corresponds to observations in bin(s):",
