    "explanation": "The correct answer is C. The weighted average maturity is calculated by weighting the number of months to maturity for each mortgage in the pool by the percentage of the outstanding mortgage balance relative to the outstanding amount of all the mortgages in the pool, as shown in the following equation:\n\n𝑊\n𝐴\n𝑀\n=\n𝑀\n𝑀\n𝐴\n(\n𝐶\n𝐵\n𝐴\n∑\n𝐶\n𝐵\n)\n+\n𝑀\n𝑀\n𝐵\n(\n𝐶\n𝐵\n𝐵\n∑\n𝐶\n𝐵\n)\n+\n𝑀\n𝑀\n𝐶\n(\n𝐶\n𝐵\n𝐶\n∑\n𝐶\n𝐵\n)\n\n\n+\n𝑀\n𝑀\n𝐷\n(\n𝐶\n𝐵\n𝐷\n∑\n𝐶\n𝐵\n)\n+\n𝑀\n𝑀\n𝐸\n(\n𝐶\n𝐵\n𝐸\n∑\n𝐶\n𝐵\n)\n𝑊\n𝐴\n𝑀\n=\n140\n(\n83\n,\n000\n1\n,\n496\n,\n000\n)\n+\n192\n(\n193\n,\n000\n1\n,\n496\n,\n000\n)\n+\n240\n(\n315\n,\n000\n1\n,\n496\n,\n000\n)\n\n\n+\n144\n(\n357\n,\n000\n1\n,\n496\n,\n000\n)\n+\n324\n(\n548\n,\n000\n1\n,\n496\n,\n000\n)\nWAM = 236 months.\n\nA is incorrect because it is calculated by averaging the months to maturity for the five mortgages, rather than calculating their weighted average.\n\nB is incorrect because it is calculated by weighting the number of months to maturity for each mortgage in the pool by the percentage of the beginning mortgage balance relative to the beginning amount of all the mortgages in the pool, not by the current balances."
